# Export Convention

Use named exports exclusively. Default exports are prohibited.

## Rules

1. **Named Exports Only**: Always use `export const` or `export function`
2. **No Default Exports**: Never use `export default`
3. **Export Public Types**: All public interfaces and types must be exported

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ Good
export const Button: React.FC<ButtonProps> = () => { ... };
export interface ButtonProps { ... }
export type ButtonVariant = 'solid' | 'outlined' | 'text';

// ❌ Bad
const Button = () => { ... };
export default Button;
```

## Index Files

Re-export components from `index.ts`:

```ts
// ✅ Good
export { Button } from './Button';
export type { ButtonProps } from './Button';
```
